main event: Three witnesses in Green Bay, Wisconsin observed a bright orangish-yellow light for approximately 10 minutes on 11 September 1968.
interesting points: The object was seen traveling NNE,The observers were John and Margaret Stealer along with Andrew,The conclusion considered the object to potentially be a hot air balloon,The sighting was reported to Don Stuerger at the Green Bay Police Department,There was no evidence presented to confirm or deny the sighting's identification.
sighted object: a bright orangish-yellow light in the sky
witness description: Andrew, a theatrical promoter, along with John and Margaret Stealer
